mitre_attack_techniques.signature_description: An adversary may attempt to get detailed information about the operating system and hardware, including version, patches, hotfixes, service packs, and architecture.
Adversaries may communicate using application layer protocols to avoid detection/network filtering by blending in with existing traffic.
Adversaries may interact with the native OS application programming interface (API) to execute behaviors.
Adversaries may inject code into processes in order to evade process-based defenses as well as possibly elevate privileges.
Adversaries may modify file time attributes to hide new or changes to existing files.
Adversaries may delete or modify artifacts generated within systems to remove evidence of their presence or hinder defenses.
Allocates memory with a write watch (potentially for evading sandboxes)
Creates guard pages, often used to prevent reverse engineering and debugging
Binary contains a suspicious time stamp
Queries the volume information (name, serial number etc) of a device

signature_matches.name: contains PDB path
signature_matches.description: executable/pe/pdb
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: contains PDB path
    namespace: executable/pe/pdb
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: file
      dynamic: file
    examples:
      - 464EF2CA59782CE697BC329713698CCC  # level32.exe
  features:
    - string: /:\\.*\.pdb/

signature_matches.name: compiled to the .NET platform
signature_matches.description: runtime/dotnet
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: compiled to the .NET platform
    namespace: runtime/dotnet
    authors:
      - william.ballenthin@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: file
      dynamic: file
    examples:
      - b9f5bd514485fb06da39beff051b9fdc
  features:
    - or:
      - format: dotnet
      - import: mscoree._CorExeMain
      - import: mscoree._corexemain
      - import: mscoree._CorDllMain
      - import: mscoree._cordllmain

signature_matches.name: unmanaged call
signature_matches.description: runtime : managed code calls unmanaged (native) code, often seen in .NET
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: unmanaged call
    namespace: runtime
    authors:
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    description: managed code calls unmanaged (native) code, often seen in .NET
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: unsupported
  features:
    - or:
      - characteristic: unmanaged call
      - match: unmanaged call via dynamic PInvoke in .NET
      - api: System.Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal::GetDelegateForFunctionPointer

signature_matches.name: (internal) .NET file limitation
signature_matches.description:
internal/limitation/dynamic : This dynamic analysis trace describes a .NET file.

capa rules are not yet tuned for the .NET runtime, 
so its analysis may be incomplete or misleading.
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: (internal) .NET file limitation
    namespace: internal/limitation/dynamic
    authors:
      - "@v1bh475u"
    description: |
      This dynamic analysis trace describes a .NET file.

      capa rules are not yet tuned for the .NET runtime, 
      so its analysis may be incomplete or misleading.
    scopes:
      static: file
      dynamic: file
    examples:
      - 2f8a79b12a7a989ac7e5f6ec65050036588a92e65aeb6841e08dc228ff0e21b4_min_archive.zip
  features:
    - or:
      - format: dotnet
      - import: mscoree._CorExeMain
      - import: mscoree._corexemain
      - import: mscoree._CorDllMain
      - import: mscoree._cordllmain
